         <entry xml:id="Slips_SkyeSMacLeodslips-idp164417152">
            <form>
               <orth>mealtrach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Notes: ‘rud a’ fàs anns a’ ghainmhich, ga chleachdadh airson sgùradh.’ (Heard in Harris.)</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SkyeSMacLeodslips-idp164414776">
            <form>
               <orth>iomchair</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: ag iomchair air. Notes: accusing, complaining.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SkyeSMacLeodslips-idp164413264">
            <form>
               <orth>ad</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: Tha iad dìreach anns na h-adaibh. Notes: used of people who are very alike.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SkyeSMacLeodslips-idp164411752">
            <form>
               <orth>ciamhair</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: Tha ciamhair ort. Notes: ‘hood wrapped round the head’. (Heard by Mrs MacLeod from C. Shaw, Tarbert, Harris in 1979.)</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_SkyeSMacLeodslips-idp164410672">
            <form>
               <orth>éigear</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: éigear odhar. Notes: term of abuse. ‘Ga chleachdadh mu dhuine a bhiodh tu a’ càineadh’.</def>
         </entry>
